# Exclude the standalone neo4j knowledge-graph pipeline (lives beside root).
# tree_walk.py + its build scripts + emitted graph results.
tree_walk.py
scripts/
graph.json
graph.gexf
graph_summaries/
frontend/graph.json

# NOTE: tools/ is hardcoded into the MCP binary's default-ignore set
# (alongside scripts/docs/keys/logs). .cbmignore negation (!tools/) does NOT
# override it, and the indexer does not follow symlinks. The tool *callers*
# and the _LazyToolRef / workflow_groups machinery are still in the graph;
# the tool *implementation bodies* are not. No config workaround exists.
